<br>
Would you allow our mez to be removed if we could get 2 group chants to replace it? (Haste and AF chant say, not End chant, let's not go there on this thread)<br>
<br>
I am curious if the Skalds at large would get rid of this ability in order to become more group friendly, especially when there is more than one Skald in the group.  <br>
<br>
Post opinions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Rosey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/18/02 8:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Opinions needed</span><hr size=1> Roseanne,<br>
<br>
I would be strongly opposed to such a move.<br>
<br>
1. We rely heavily on our instas to beat certain classes, having one less insta cast reduces our overall effectiveness.<br>
<br>
2. Skalds have very little defense as a viking class, but in a 2 on 1 situation, we are able to mezz one, and fight the other.  This gives skalds a unique &quot;defense&quot; in any small group battles that doesn't always work, but when it does, it's nice to lean on.<br>
<br>
3. It's actully quite useful in PvE for both soloing, escaping mobs, etc. Secondary CC for a group is important, and is great as an &quot;insta peel&quot;.<br>
<br>
4. DD/DD/swing/mezz is a way for skalds to actually try and fight many other classes in RvR.  Without this, we rely more heavily on our defense (which is very, very low) since we'll be fighting longer.  That's a bad thing for a skald.<br>
<br>
5. The versatility of a Skald in RvR is legendary..being able to insta CC allows us to remove one opponent, for a short time, from the fight.  Since we don't kill as fast as serkers, and don't last as long as warriors, this give us an added benefit to our groups in RvR.  Multiple skalds w/multiple mezz, it's nice.<br>
<br>
6. It's one of our &quot;chasedown&quot; abilities.  Without it, all we have is snare.  We are the premier chasedown of midgard, again, we lose out here.<br>
<br>
This would be a &quot;nerf&quot; in my opinion.  While skalds don't offer a lot to a group in terms of chants, we DO offer them dmg add, runspeed, and the ability to take out casters in seconds <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I prefer a skald-heavy group, and I think what we add to a group is a very solid offensive runspeed class that relies on speed mezz and snare to stay alive.<br>
<br>
I think if they made the resist chants like pallys, we'd have that second group chant that might make us better group-mates in RvR.<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=etzel>Etzel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/18/02 8:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:Opinions needed</span><hr size=1> Hell no, my mez has saved me on so many occasions (in PvE &amp; RvR) it's insane. If i'm chasing people down I might snare first then mez to gain more space between them and the group, an incoming rush i'll pick one of the lead guys just because he's more likely to be dangerous (or try to pick out the Hib suicide mana bombs using MOC :/ ), if I get a Hero by mistake i'll mez and run :-), I think you get the idea.<br>
