<br>
Removing mez from skalds would be a very bad move imo, regardless of what we would get in return.<br>
<br>
Both an endurance song and haste song would be welcome additions to our BS line; I would be willing to trade in the song of rest for one of them. An alternative is to combine songs... rest/end, heat/cold, etc..  However, one thing to bear in mind is that if we do get either one of these new songs, a skald's role will be closer to that of a support class.  If we do get new songs that support a group, we probably won't get things such as increased hitpoints, specable shield, or more spec pts for increased weapon/parry.<br>
<br>
Since Mythic really hasn't defined the role of a skald; perhaps they are waiting to see what role we would perfer.  What do we ultimately want a skald to be?  Hybrid Meleer, or Support Class? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugnagrakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gnagrakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/18/02 12:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mez</span><hr size=1> I do not agree that Mythic &quot;hasn't defined the role of a Skald&quot;. They've done it since the start.<br>
