Because I think most of us chose the skald because of the way the class played and felt at the beginnng of the game, a battle oriented warrior poet, a strong fighting class with some utility.<br>
If we had wanted to play a support/ AFK+stick taxi, we would have chosen to play a bard. Or a healer, cleric, warden ...<br>
However, the sad thing is that Mythic seems to want to pigeonhole us into a more and more &quot;support&quot; (well taxi, we don't have another adequate support song), and less and less fighting (1.52 &quot;resist patch&quot; that crippled out shout DMG, goodies for other melees in 1.53 ...).<br>
If anything I'd like to get a slight melee (esp. defensive) boost (more spec points for parry ? evade 2 ? speccable shield ?) and/or the recognition that the &quot;caster patch&quot; reduced our damaging ability without the large compensations most of the other caster classes got.<br>
<br>
Dargaard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/19/02 5:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Precision</span><hr size=1> Besides, our mez shout is an integral part of group strategies in PvE. In short, we don't have enough casters to make a lot of AE groups (they do exist in Midgard, but they are rare), and the secondary CC class is *rare* (and more often than not best employed in the forementioned AE groups). Basically, the skald plays by default the role of the backup/emergency/secondary CC in PvE group.<br>
<br>
I don't want more &quot;support&quot;, except a change on the rest song to make it more useful. What I want is either a normalization of skald melee ability (particularly defensive) to the actual level of other combat hybrids (that's the template skalds are based on, like it or not), or a way to fix our shout damages to the level they were at in the past.<br>
