ont color=#ff0000>(9/19/02 11:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Remove Mez?</span><hr size=1> I've pretty much been playing a skald from the beginning of DAoC. I've only recently started playing other classes, but I learned how to play DAoC and a skald at the same time. One thing I can say is that once I started using my mez effectively in pve, primarily solo, I was able to do a whole lot more. I would hate to see mez removed from skalds for that very reason.<br>
<br>
As for RvR, I can barely solo an assassin. If I manage to catch two casters, I can mez one, kill the other, then kill the mezzed.. maybe. However, I have used it effectively to chase down runners a LOT. That's my favorite and primary use of mez in rvr.<br>
<br>
I would prefer to see changes to the skald to make us even more effective at chasing down runners. It's not like we can stand toe to toe to most classes anyway, so let us make a difference where we shine and make us more effective at it. Primarily, keep the speed chant from failing at all for the skald. Lose group speed for combat, but let the skald keep it. You're already giving up your damage add to leave speed on during the combat, let's make it worth something. I would be willing to sacrifice a shorter duration (as if 30s isn't short enough.. yeesh) for a much longer range and shorter cast time on the mez though. Give us a 10s recast and a 20s duration. The 2nd mez will only last 10s anyway and a 3rd 5s.<br>
<br>
Those are just my few random thoughts on mez.<br>
<br>
Rogenwald<br>
50 skald - Tristan<br>
